      <pubtit>High-spatiotemporal-resolution mapping of global urban change from 1985 to 2015</pubtit>
      <p><img src="http://localhost:4000/images/pubpic/SFnews.png" class="img-responsive" width="33%" style="float: left" /></p>
      <p>This rate of urban expansion is four times greater than previous reputable estimates from worldwide individual cities, suggesting an unprecedented rate of global urbanization. It is notably faster than that of population growth, indicating that the urban land area already exceeds what is needed to sustain population growth.</p>
      <p><em>Xiaoping Liu, Yinghuai Huang, Xiaocong Xu, Xuecao Li, Xia Li* , Philippe Ciais, Peirong Lin, Kai Gong, Alan D. Ziegler, Anping Chen, Peng Gong, Jun Chen, Guohua Hu, Yimin Chen, Shaojian Wang, Qiusheng Wu, Kangning Huang, Lyndon Estes, <b>Zhenzhong Zeng* </b></em></p>
